arts.ttl: Exeter City end Wycombe's winning run but let two-goal lead slip
arts.sum: Exeter City ended Wycombe Wanderers’ 11 game winning run but were left ruing letting a two goal lead slip. City doubled the lead midway through the first half when Jack McMillan was quickest to react from a corner and poke home from a yard out.

arts.ttl: Wycombe’s winning streak comes to end after draw at Exeter
arts.sum: The Chairboys battled back from 2-0 down.

arts.ttl: Exeter City ready to try and end Wycombe's 11 game winning run
arts.sum: We know it's going to be a tough game, but we're at home so we put pressure on ourselves to win. "I saw them live at Stockport recently when they won 5-0 so I saw them at their very best and we know what their threats are.

arts.ttl: Exeter City Women go third after another dominant win
arts.sum: Four different players - Zoe Watkins, Sarah Stacey, Georgie Barbour-Gresham, and Phoebe Baker - all found the net for the Grecians, who built on a strong first-half display to claim three points. Emily Toogood came closest with a back-post header that skimmed just wide, while moments later, she nearly found the net directly from an in-swinging corner, forcing the keeper to palm the ball over the crossbar.

arts.ttl: Jake Richards has 'best game for Exeter City' as teen stars
arts.sum: Saturday’s outing was the first time the self-confessed City fan had played outside the EFL Trophy this season, but manager Gary Caldwell said that performances in training as well as the U21 Premier League Cup games he has featured in meant he deserved his chance. The 17-year-old made his first appearance for City this season outside of the EFL Trophy and didn’t look at all out of place in the 2-0 FA Cup win over Chesterfield.

arts.ttl: FA Cup third round draw LIVE: Updates as Liverpool, Manchester United and Premier League sides learn fate
arts.sum: A total of 64 sides will found out their opponents for the next round, with all Championship and Premier League sides entering the draw
